d:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"Why this order? Named targets trump skill matching because explicit is better than implicit. If a ceremony explicitly says “send this to ava”, we should respect that even if another agent also declares the same skill. The default is last because it is a catch-all — it should only fire when nothing more specific matches."}]
